 should generally protect the minimal core required set of headers:<br />From/To/Date/Subject/Message-ID etc. Not the headers that are<br />intentionally going to be rewritten by any list you might want to post<br />to.<br /><br />               Linus "hate spam, try to fix dkim" Torvalds<br /><br />On Wed, Jul 17, 2019 at 12:20 PM Alexandre GRIVEAUX<br />&lt;agriveaux&#64;deutnet.info&gt; wrote:<br />&gt;<br />&gt; Add the devicetree nodes for the I2C core of the JZ4780 SoC, disabled<br />&gt; by default.<br />..<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
